channel.description:
[center]200 Meter Peanut Dash Player[/center] [center]Neopets game located at [url=http://neopets.com/games/puppyblew.phtml]http://neopets.com/games/puppyblew.phtml[/url].[/center] [center]Average NP per run: 720[/center]
Current Version: 0.1
[ul][li]Shoots the peanut[/li] [li]Jumps over the logs[/li] [li]Catches the peanut with a backflip[/li][/ul]
To use: [u]Download attatchment, open the game, select the window. Wait for the game to load, and run the script.[/u]
[b]Like it? Doesn't work? Drop me a line at [email]Aftermath.96@gmail.com[/email][/b] If you download, please post here and tell me how much you like it. :P Or not.
If you all get any problems or have any suggestions, tell me and I'll put them in the next version.

item.title: 200 Meter Peanut Dash Player
item.dc:creator: @sslleeaakkiinngg sslleeaakkiinngg
item.description:
@sslleeaakkiinngg wrote:

If people don’t have SRL,I edited Aftermath’s script and it works perfect try this:[scar]//200 Meter Peanut Dash Player - By Aftermath 96
//Neopets game located at http://neopets.com/games/puppyblew.phtml
//Play the game in a normal (800 x 600) window.
//Every time you play, open a new game window.
//Version: 0.1 Light With Comments
//Aftermath_96 on http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/
//Edited my sslleeaakkiinng,Instructions:Run script(make sure you have num lock key on),
//run script press up key,watch it go,after it catches the peanut pause the script,
//then run it again,repeat this every time you use it
program PeanutPlayer;
//Missing this include? Get it at http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php?topic=3617.0

var BPlayGame {Play Game Button}, BNextRound {Next Round Button},Log {The Logs}, Clouds {Clouds When Running},x,y: Integer;
procedure StartGame;
begin
If(FindDTM(BPlayGame,x,y,190,190,470,270))Then
ActivateClient;
ClearDebug;
end;
procedure PlayGame;
begin
repeat
SendArrowSilent(3); //Hit left and right to charge up the bar
SendArrowSilent(1);
until(FindColor(x,y,255,160,350,160,353)); //Wait for the energy bar to turn red

SendArrowSilent(0); //Hit Up (Release Peanut)

repeat
  Wait(1000); //Wait for the intro to stop
until(FindDTM(Clouds,x,y,340,30,430,90)); //Look for the clouds in the main part


if(not(FindColorTolerance(x,y,16764622,330,200,360,250,20)))Then
  begin
    repeat
      SendArrowSilentWait(1,10); //Move right until the dog is under the peanut
    until(FindColorTolerance(x,y,16764622,330,200,360,250,20));
  end;

repeat
if(FindDTM(Log,x,y,400,250,490,310))Then
  begin
    SendArrowSilent(0); //Jump over logs
    SendArrowSilent(1);
  end;
until(FindColorTolerance(x,y,6518656,300,130,390,300,3));
    SendArrowSilent(1); //Catch the peanut in a backflip
    SendArrowSilent(3);
    SendArrowSilent(1);
    SendArrowSilent(3);
    SendArrowSilent(0);

end;
procedure NextRound;
begin
repeat
wait(1000+random(17));
until(FindDTM(BNextRound,x,y,60,80,250,140));
end;
begin
BPlayGame := DTMFromString(‘78DA63CC63646060076224F0FFFF7F300D136’ +
‘54C02B2BEA32861D8B0014D4D3590F515550DC34C0654350598E6’ +
‘CC5A7E03554D0E90258DEA1E657149143500BFED0D9F’);
BNextRound := DTMFromString(‘78DA639CCBC0C050C18002BCB46418B880342’ +
‘310FF0702C6262023970103C0D48000E35A2091872A2FCEC382AA’ +
‘A6154834A0AA7152164255B31B4834A1B9474306450D000BFF0B5’ +
‘6’);
Clouds := DTMFromString(‘78DA636C65646070674001BF7EFF651001D24’ +
‘01986FF40C0980F6479A0AAA958FA12AE0604186B802C0B5435F6’ +
‘8D0F51D54C06B22C51D538D4A1A999036439A2AAA95CF911554D3’ +
‘B90E58BAA26B2FB158A1A00A1431554’);
Log := DTMFromString(‘78DA63F465606090616440066EA6520C5C401’ +
‘A24FA1F081803800C4154354A52BC703520C0E88069CE94423354’ +
‘35E140429A801A907BB4F1AB01006FCC0ADD’);

{Begin Main Loop}
StartGame;
PlayGame;
NextRound;
PlayGame;
NextRound;
PlayGame;
{.End Main Loop.}

end.[/scar]
Sorry Aftermath if I edited it.I just thought that if you haven’t edited it,I would do it.[br][size=1]Posted at: October 08, 2006, 03:42:47 PM[/size][hr]I put the instructions on the top under all of Aftermath’s stuff.
